---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '@/components/Section.astro';
import Reveal from '@/components/Reveal.astro';
import Button from '@/components/Button.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '@/components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import MarketplaceCTA from '@/components/MarketplaceCTA.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import { SITE } from '@/lib/site';

import markPortrait from '@/assets/showcase/mark-faith-tolkien-dealer-portrait.jpg';

const PATH = '/ebook';

const trail = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Tolkien Collector’s Guide E-book', url: PATH },
];

const subject = encodeURIComponent('Free Tolkien Collector’s Guide e-book');
const mailto = `mailto:${SITE.email}?subject=${subject}`;
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Free Tolkien Collector’s Guide E-book | Festival Art & Books"
  description="Get Mark Faith’s free 26-page Tolkien Collector’s Guide e-book: practical advice on buying and collecting rare Tolkien books. Free with any purchase or with the newsletter."
>
  <Section tone="midnight" space="md">
    <Breadcrumbs trail={trail} class="text-[var(--color-parchment)]/70" />
    <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[1.4fr_1fr] lg:items-center">
      <Reveal class="max-w-2xl">
        <p class="font-ui text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[var(--color-gold-300)]">
          Free collector’s guide
        </p>
        <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl text-[var(--color-parchment)] sm:text-5xl">
          The Tolkien Collector’s Guide
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 font-text text-xl leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-parchment)]/85">
          Mark’s Tolkien Collector’s Guide is free when you buy something from us, and the
          monthly newsletter is free too. It is his way of sharing twenty-five years of
          specialist knowledge, to enhance your collecting, save you time, and help you
          make better choices.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <Button href={mailto} variant="gold" size="lg">Email Mark for your free copy</Button>
        </div>
      </Reveal>
      <Reveal mode="fade" delay={120}>
        <figure class="overflow-hidden rounded-[var(--radius)] border border-[var(--color-gold-600)]/30">
          <Image
            src={markPortrait}
            alt="Mark Faith, author of the free Tolkien Collector’s Guide e-book"
            widths={[400, 700]}
            sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 30vw, 100vw"
            class="w-full object-cover"
          />
        </figure>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section tone="paper" width="prose">
    <Reveal>
      <p class="font-ui text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[var(--color-gold-600)]">
        From the introduction
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl text-[var(--color-midnight-900)] sm:text-4xl">
        A note from Mark
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 font-text text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-text)]">
        <p>
          Thank you for investing your time in this little guide. I hope it will enhance
          your Tolkien collecting experience, save you time, and help you make better
          choices. Many people consider their Tolkien collecting just a hobby, but for
          most it’s very much a paying one; I financed my first collection by reselling
          spare copies. Tolkien early editions are easy to identify, but prices vary
          widely, so it can be tricky knowing what to pay for a particular copy.
        </p>
        <p>
          I have been a specialist Tolkien dealer for twenty-five years, and was a private
          collector before that. I am not an antiquarian-book or literature expert; I know
          Tolkien books as a personal reading passion. I think I know more than most
          dealers because I have specialised so narrowly and handled thousands of copies
          myself. I am not a broker; I hold dozens of rare editions in stock, ready to
          buy, and sell some books on consignment for customers.
        </p>
        <p>
          At the core of my business is a true passion for the author and the fantasy
          genre. I am a fan, completely open and willing to discuss collecting and the
          works themselves. This guide is my way of sharing what I have learned. Please
          feel free to email your own tips, anecdotes and suggestions so I can improve
          future editions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Reveal>
  </Section>

  <Section tone="parchment" width="prose" space="md">
    <Reveal>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-[var(--color-midnight-900)] sm:text-4xl">
        How to get the e-book
      </h2>
      <ol class="mt-6 space-y-4 font-text text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-text)]">
        <li>
          <span class="font-ui text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--color-gold-600)]">Step 1:</span>
          Email Mark at
          <a
            href={mailto}
            class="text-[var(--color-midnight-900)] underline decoration-[var(--color-gold-600)]/50 underline-offset-4 hover:text-[var(--color-oxblood-600)]"
          >{SITE.email}</a>
          and ask for the free Tolkien Collector’s Guide.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-ui text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--color-gold-600)]">Step 2:</span>
          You can also join the free monthly newsletter at the same time.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-ui text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--color-gold-600)]">Step 3:</span>
          The full guide is included free with any purchase from the shop.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <Button href={mailto} variant="primary" size="lg">Request the free e-book</Button>
      </div>
    </Reveal>
  </Section>

  <Section tone="surface" space="md">
    <MarketplaceCTA heading="Browse the collection" tone="paper" />
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
